					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of the Timmarāju temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1554 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1476, Ānanda, Adhika-Āshāḍha śu. 15, Lunar eclipse,</hi> regularly corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1554 A.D., June 15, (Friday).</hi></p>						

						<p>The epigraph is damaged and it seems to register the gift of three <hi rend="italic">varāhas</hi> payable to them in the village Bētāpalle included in Pullēṭimāgāṇi in Jagatāpi-Gutti-sīma to god Tirumaladēva of the same village by the <hi rend="italic">dommaris</hi> (acrobats) for the merit of their twenty four families.</p>						

						</summary>
